18. paenula,' a rough woollen or leather cloak worn in rainy weather: cp. Juv. V. 79 cum. . .mull0 stillaret paenula nimbo, with Mayor’s note. The Greek form φαινόλης is perhaps only an attempt at assimilation from the better-established φελόνης : cp. Tisch. and W. H. on 2 Tim. iv. 13. Nothing is known of the derivation of the word in either language.
